modules.description: Maps a function over the bytes in place, modifying the original byte sequence. Operates on the bytes type, applying a character transformation to each element. Useful for in-place character encoding or decoding tasks.

Generates a mapping from characters to integers and vice versa, taking a string to create a tuple of the string and an array of corresponding integer values. It retrieves the integer value of a character from the mapping and converts an integer back to its corresponding character. Used to encode and decode characters within a predefined character set.

Provides 63-bit integer arithmetic with efficient encoding and decoding of values as fixed-length big-endian byte sequences. Supports operations for converting between integers and byte arrays, ensuring consistent representation across systems. Examples include serializing a 63-bit integer to a 8-byte array and reconstructing the value from its encoded form. Enables reliable data transmission and storage of large integer values within a fixed bit width.

Encodes and decodes values between a custom type and string representations, supporting safe conversion from strings with option results. Works with an extensible variant type that represents different encoding schemes. Used to serialize configuration settings and parse user input into structured data.

Transforms byte sequences in place using a provided function, enabling direct modification of character data. Constructs bidirectional character-to-integer mappings from a given string, allowing efficient encoding and decoding operations. For example, it can convert a byte array to a base58 string by applying a transformation and using a custom character set. It also supports reversing the process, translating encoded integers back into their original byte representation.

Encodes and decodes 63-bit integers as fixed-length byte arrays, enabling consistent representation and transmission of large numeric values. Provides functions to convert between integers and byte arrays, ensuring reliable storage and reconstruction. Operations include serializing a 63-bit integer into an 8-byte sequence and parsing it back accurately. This supports applications requiring precise numeric handling within constrained bit widths.

Encodes and decodes strings using self-identifying base encodings, returning the associated encoding scheme alongside the decoded data. Works with strings formatted according to the multibase specification, including base16, base32, and base64 variants. Used to process encoded data streams where the encoding method is embedded within the string itself.

Encodes and decodes strings using various base-encoding schemes, returning results with specific error cases for unsupported encodings or invalid input. Operates on strings and encoding types representing different base-encoding formats. Used to process multibase-encoded data, such as converting binary data to a base-encoded string or extracting the original data from a multibase string.
